Mozilla Public License Version 2.0
==================================

1. Definitions
--------------

1.1. "Contributor"
    means each individual or legal entity that creates, contributes to
    the creation of, or owns Covered Software.

1.2. "Contributor Version"
    means the contribution of a Contributor and the Covered Software
    that results from adding that contribution.

1.3. "Covered Software"
    means Source Code Form to which the initial Contributor has attached
    the notice in Exhibit A, the Executable Form of such Source Code
    Form, and Modifications of such Source Code Form, in each case
    including portions thereof.

1.4. "Incompatible With Secondary Licenses"
    means
    (a) that the initial Contributor has attached the notice described
        in Exhibit B to the Covered Software; or
    (b) that the Covered Software was made available under the terms of
        version 1.1 or earlier of the License, but not also under the
        terms of a Secondary License.

1.5. "Executable Form"
    means any form of the work other than Source Code Form.

1.6. "Larger Work"
    means a work that combines Covered Software with other material, in
    a separate file or files, that is not Covered Software.

1.7. "License"
    means this document.

1.8. "Licensable"
    means having the right to grant, to the maximum extent possible,
    whether at the time of the initial grant or subsequently, any and
    all of the rights conveyed by this License.

1.9. "Modifications"
    means any of the following:
    (a) any file, or portion thereof, that results from an addition to,
        deletion from, or modification of the contents of Covered
        Software; or
    (b) any new file, or portion thereof, that contains any Covered
        Software.

1.10. "Patent Claims" of a Contributor
    means any patent claim(s), including cost of defense, warranty
    disclaimers, and indemnifications, made by such Contributor to You
    relating to its Contributor Version (excluding claims that relate
    solely to modifications of files made by others even though included
    in such Contributor Version); provided that the Patent Claims of a
    Contributor shall not include claims relating to any code that a
    Contributor is required to contribute to Covered Software under
    an applicable agreement or law.

1.11. "Source Code Form"
    means the form of the work preferred for making modifications.

1.12. "You" (or "Your")
    means an individual or a legal entity exercising rights under this
    License. For legal entities, "You" includes any other entity that
    controls, is controlled by, or is under common control with You. For
    purposes of this definition, "control" means (a) the power, direct
    or indirect, to cause the direction or management of such entity,
    whether by contract or otherwise, or (b) ownership of fifty percent
    (50%) or more of the outstanding shares, or (c) beneficial ownership
    of such entity.

