non-exclusive license:

(a) under intellectual property rights (other than patent or trademark)
    Licensable by such Contributor to use, reproduce, modify, display,
    perform, sublicense and distribute the Modifications created by such
    Contributor (or portions thereof) either on an unmodified basis,
    with other Modifications, as Covered Software or as part of a Larger
    Work; and

(b) under Patent Claims of such Contributor that are necessarily
    infringed by the creation, using, selling, offering for sale,
    having made, importing, or otherwise transferring either unmodified
    or modified versions of the Contributor Version (excluding combining
    the Covered Software with other code not derived from the Covered
    Software that, by itself, would not infringe the Patent Claims of
    the Contributor), to make, use, sell, offer for sale, have made,
    import, and otherwise transfer the Covered Software.

(c) If You are an entity, the grants in Section 2.1(a) and (b) are
    conditioned upon Your not maintaining any competitive disclosure of
    the Covered Software to third parties who are not under an
    obligation of confidentiality with respect to the Covered Software.
    However, You may retain a list of designated representatives who are
    permitted to maintain competitive disclosures of the Covered
    Software under an obligation of confidentiality containing the same
    information as Your competitive disclosure, provided that such list
    (1) does not identify anyone by their name or other identifying
    information, only by role or position, and (2) is updated at least
    annually to reflect persons in those roles and positions, and (3) is
    made available for inspection, upon reasonable request, by any
    Licensee of the Covered Software hereunder who wishes to enforce
    Section 2.1(c).

2.2. Effective Date

The licenses granted in Section 2.1 with respect to any Covered Software
become effective on the date Contributor first distributes such Covered
Software under the terms of this License.

2.3. Limitations on Grant Scope

The licenses granted in this Section 2 are the only rights granted under
this License. No additional rights or licenses will be implied from the
distribution or licensing of Covered Software under this License.
Notwithstanding Section 2.1(b) above, no patent license is granted by a
Contributor:

(a) for any code that a Contributor has removed from Covered Software;
    or

(b) for infringements caused by: (i) Your and any other third party's
    modifications of Covered Software, or (ii) the combination of its
    Covered Software with other code not derived from the Covered
    Software.

2.4. Licenses and Notices

If the Covered Software is "network transparent software", the Covered
Software may be distributed under the AGPL v3 or any later version as an
exception to the foregoing provisions of the License. However, in all
other respects, the terms of the License still apply to the Covered
Software and must be honored.

If You include a notice in a header file of the Covered Software to
indicate the exclusion of warranties or limitation of liability, such
notice must:

(a) inform recipients that the Covered Software is governed by the terms
    of the License; and

(b) inform recipients that You, the Contributor(s), are free from
    liability or indemnity for damages.

(c) state the URL from which the Covered Software code may be obtained.

If You distribute Covered Software in Executable Form under a previous
version of this License without including the Source Code Form and a
means of obtaining a copy thereof, You may do so provided that:

(a) You include a clear and prominent notice that states the Covered
    Software is governed by the terms of this License, and directing
    recipients to the URL where the Covered Software may be obtained;

(b) You retain in the Covered Software all copyright, patent, trademark,
    and attribution notices that were in the Source Code Form (excluding
    those notices that do not pertain to any part of the Covered
    Software);

(c) You retain a complete, unmodified copy of this License with the
    Covered Software.

2.5. Essentially Equivalent Mechanics

If You distribute Executable Form Covered Software either alone or as
part of a collection, product or compilation with other code, and under
a license of Your choice, then the option to distribute the Covered
Software under the License (Licensor's choice) remains open, provided
that Your license terms and conditions are not intended to and do not
prevent, limit or interfere with the licensee's rights granted under the
License.

3. Distribution Obligations
----------------------------

3.1. Application of License

The obligations of this Section 3 apply to the distribution of Covered
Software.

3.2. Distribution of Source Form

All distribution of Covered Software in Source Code Form, including any
Modifications that You create or to which You contribute, must be under
the terms of this License. You must inform recipients that the Source
Code Form of the Covered Software is governed by the terms of this
License, and how they can obtain a copy of this License. You may not
attempt to alter or restrict the recipients' rights in the Source Code
Form.

3.3. Distribution of Executable Form

If You distribute Covered Software in Executable Form then:

(a) such Covered Software must also be made available in Source Code
    Form, as described in Section 3.2, and You must inform recipients of
    the Executable Form how they can obtain a copy of such Source Code
    Form by reasonable means in a timely manner, at a charge no more
    than the cost of distribution to the recipient; and

(b) You may distribute such Executable Form under the terms of this
    License, or sublicense it under different terms, provided that the
    license for the Executable Form does not attempt to limit or alter
    the recipients' rights in the Source Code Form under this License.

3.4. Distribution of a Larger Work

You may create a Larger Work by combining Covered Software with other
code not governed by the terms of this License and distribute the Larger
Work as a single product. In such a case, You must ensure the
requirements of this License are fulfilled for the Covered Software.

4. Inability to Comply Due to Statute or Regulation
----------------------------------------------------

If it is impossible for You to comply with any of the terms of this
License with respect to some or all of the Covered Software due to
statute, judicial order, or regulation, then You must: (a) comply with
the terms of this License to the maximum extent possible; and (b)
describe the limitations and the code they affect. Such description must
be placed in a prominent place in the source code files that are subject
to the conditions, and must remain with those files unless otherwise
required to do so by statute or regulation. Except when otherwise
impossible due to such statute or regulation, the description must be in
both human-readable form and, if an automated processor can parse it, in
a form suitable for automated processing.

5. Termination
--------------

5.1. The rights granted under this License will terminate automatically
if You fail to comply with any of its terms.

5.2. If any Contributor includes a "NOTICE" text file with Covered
Software indicating that such Covered Software may be distributed under
the terms of any Secondary License, then any choice of such Secondary
License made by such Contributor will be non-revocable and will apply
irrespective of whether the overall composition is ultimately governed
by the Secondary License.

If such a NOTICE file exists, then unless You affirmatively elect
otherwise, by using, modifying, copying, sublicensing or distributing
the Covered Software, You agree that Your use, modification, copying,
sublicensing or distribution of the Covered Software is governed by the
terms of the Secondary License selected by such Contributor.

5.3. If You initiate litigation or any other proceeding asserting a
patent infringement claim (excluding declaratory judgment actions
brought counter to a patent infringement allegation) against any entity
(including a cross-claim or counterclaim in a lawsuit), then any patent
licenses granted to that entity under this License for that
work shall terminate as of the date such litigation or proceeding is
filed.

