---------------------------

9.1. New Versions

Mozilla Foundation is the license steward. Except as provided in Section
9.3, no one other than the license steward has the right to modify or
publish new versions of this License. Each version will be given a
distinguishing version number.

9.2. Effect of New Versions

You may distribute the Covered Software under the terms of the version
of the License under which You originally received the Covered Software,
or under the terms of any subsequent version published by the license
steward, if that version is not materially different from the version
under which You received the Covered Software.

9.3. Modified Versions

If you create software not governed by this License, or modify Covered
Software and distribute it under a license such that the responsibilities,
warranties, and liabilities of those licensing the Covered Software are
materially different from those of this License (including, without
limitation, in cases where the software is made available to third
parties as a hosted service), you must clearly mark the modifications
made to the Covered Software and avoid creating confusion regarding what
is and is not Covered Software by including in any file containing
Covered Software a prominent statement that such file is modified and is
not governed by the terms of this License.

10. Compliance
--------------

10.1. If any provision of this License is found to be unenforceable, that
provision shall be reformed to the minimum extent necessary to make it
enforceable.

11. New License Versions
------------------------

Mozilla Foundation may publish revised and/or new versions of the License
from time to time. Each new version will have a distinguishing version
